<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF7590EEFE08A437" bold="true" box="[151,385,1255,1281]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Material examined.</emphasis>
1 (sex unknown), Kokee, Kauai, 
<date id="FF97101DFF820763FD1990EEFCF2A434" box="[763,891,1255,1282]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" value="2015-07-13">13.vii.2015</date>
(stored), C.A. Johns leg., host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D5EFF820763FB3D90EEFA15A437" box="[1247,1436,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Lipochaeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acris">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FB3D90EEFA15A437" box="[1247,1436,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Lipochaeta acris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D5EFF820763FF589105FE20A413" box="[186,425,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Lipochaeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="connata" variety="acris">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF589105FF43A413" box="[186,202,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF389105FEBDA413" box="[218,308,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">connata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FE939105FE20A413" box="[369,425,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">acris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], 
<date id="FF97101DFF820763FE219102FDB5A410" box="[451,572,1291,1318]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" value="2015-06-15">15.vi.2015</date>
, CJ483 (abdomen missing) in 
<collectionCode id="ED38AE18FF820763FC7D9105FC79A410" box="[927,1008,1292,1318]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34697" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34697" name="Bishop Museum" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" type="Museum">BPBM</collectionCode>
. What remains of the specimens was mounted by placing two forewings without mountant under a coverslip and a 3/4 hindwing in capsule (
<figureCitation id="13122A58FF820763FAC49126FA19A47C" box="[1318,1424,1327,1354]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1652,1676]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,187,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-23@44.[151,1436,181,1629]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Adults of Philodoria species. A P. lipochaetaella, specimens originally described as Parectopa lipochaetae Swezey, 1946, syntype male B P. sciallactis (Meyrick, 1928) lectotype male C Paralectotype male D Paralectotype female E Male left forewing of specimen CJ164, host: Melanthera kamolensis, Maui F Same specimen, right forewing G Male right forewing of specimen CJ189, host: Melanthera kamolensis, Maui H Philodoria sp. B nr. P. sciallactis (specimen CJ483, sex unknown) right forewing, host: Lipochaeta acris, Kauai. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4681861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4681861/files/figure.png" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Fig. 24H</figureCitation>
). The head, antenna, thorax, and legs were sacrificed for molecular analysis and the abdomen is missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3336556FF820763FF25917EFDF0A4EF" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9636DDFF820763FF25917EFD7FA480" blockId="108.[151,1437,1255,1714]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF25917EFECBA4A7" bold="true" box="[199,322,1399,1425]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The forewing pattern is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D5EFF820763FD279171FC44A4A4" authority="(Meyrick)" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" box="[709,973,1399,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Parectopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sciallactis">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FD279171FCDBA4A7" box="[709,850,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">P. sciallactis</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished by the round 
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FAA89171FAE4A4AE" bold="true" box="[1354,1389,1400,1432]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
ds 
<subScript id="17AD3498FF820763FA879183FAE4A4AE" attach="left" box="[1381,1389,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
and brown 
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF049195FE84A48A" bold="true" box="[230,269,1436,1468]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
dp 
<subScript id="17AD3498FF820763FEE791A7FE84A48A" attach="left" box="[261,269,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FEA19195FEE2A48A" bold="true" box="[323,363,1436,1468]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
dp 
<subScript id="17AD3498FF820763FE8191A7FEE2A48A" attach="left" box="[355,363,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
meeting at median line (
<figureCitation id="13122A58FF820763FD639192FD63A480" box="[641,746,1435,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1652,1676]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,187,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-23@44.[151,1436,181,1629]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Adults of Philodoria species. A P. lipochaetaella, specimens originally described as Parectopa lipochaetae Swezey, 1946, syntype male B P. sciallactis (Meyrick, 1928) lectotype male C Paralectotype male D Paralectotype female E Male left forewing of specimen CJ164, host: Melanthera kamolensis, Maui F Same specimen, right forewing G Male right forewing of specimen CJ189, host: Melanthera kamolensis, Maui H Philodoria sp. B nr. P. sciallactis (specimen CJ483, sex unknown) right forewing, host: Lipochaeta acris, Kauai. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4681861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4681861/files/figure.png" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Fig. 24H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
