<subSubSection id="C3336556FF820763FF259259FBEAA787" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9636DDFF820763FF259259FBEAA787" blockId="108.[151,1437,1255,1714]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF259259FEB2A75C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1616,1642]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</emphasis>
Judging from forewing characters, we consider this species as a unique species. But because parts of its body are missing, we tentatively call it 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D5EFF820763FD84927AFD56A7BB" box="[614,735,1651,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Philodoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FD84927AFD56A7BB" box="[614,735,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Philodoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. B near 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D5EFF820763FCBB927DFC6FA7BB" box="[857,998,1651,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Parectopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sciallactis">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FCBB927DFC6FA7BB" box="[857,998,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">P. sciallactis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We hope that future studies will search 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D5EFF820763FF75929EFEDDA787" box="[151,340,1687,1713]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Lipochaeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acris">
<emphasis id="B95DEACFFF820763FF75929EFEDDA787" box="[151,340,1687,1713]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Lipochaeta acris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plants at Kokee, Kauai, so that additional specimens can be obtained.
</paragraph>
